Tom Gores (Born: Tewfiq Georgious Arabic: توفيق جورجيوس) (born July 31, 1964) is an Israeli-American businessman and investor. He is a billionaire with an estimated current net worth of $3.9 billion according to the 2015 Forbes list of World's Billionaires.[3] He is the founder of Platinum Equity, a private equity firm with headquarters in Beverly Hills. On June 1, 2011, Tom Gores and Platinum Equity became the owners of the National Basketball Association’s (NBA) Detroit Pistons.



